				When my guild planning on raids, we have comments on both side. But the turn out is, post a message here has no harm even not useful and obvious it does not need a great effort to post a message. So we post here.  <br>  <br> We respect guilds who will respect the reservation system, our raid planning are for them to see. If you do not respect the system or think that it not works, fine to me. But for those posted messages to reserve raids, we will not go the place on the reserve days and we also not want to see any of those guilds on our reserve days. <br>  <br> Sometimes we may go up planes without reservation if we know that there are no annouced schedule. That means we may crush into someone else raids. If the guild in planes think that it should be first come first serve, then we will leave and if next time the order is reversed, we come first, we will also request them to leave. If the one in planes think that share is ok, we may share and next time we will let them come in to share also. <br>  <br> That is what we can do to respect other players' playing styles here. <br>  <br> Raid planning does not means we own the place that day. If guilds or group of people do have same planning on that day, feel free to contact us.		

